class Solution {
    public long minEnd(int n, int x) {
        long m = n - 1;
        long mask = x;
        long bit = 1;
        while (m > 0) {
            if ((mask & bit) == 0) {
                mask |= (m & 1) * bit;
                m >>= 1;
            }
            bit <<= 1;
        }
        return mask;
    }
}
```
efficiency: HIGH
time complexity: O(log(n + x))
space complexity: O(1)
energy implications: LOW
explanation: Treat the strictly increasing sequence as x plus a set of bit patterns that do not overlap with x’s set bits. The required sequence length n is achieved by interpreting n-1 as a binary number and embedding its bits into the zero positions of x, producing the smallest possible last element.

